                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1385" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1385" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1385" type="surname" value="VANDERSTEEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1385" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES VANDERSTEEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a builder, and live in Bethnal-green. On the 23rd of August I was passing the workhouse in Whitechapel-road, and felt something at my pocket—I turned round and saw the prisoner putting my handkerchief in his right-hand trowsers pocket—I laid hold of</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183808200211"></xptr>
               <p>him and asked what he had done—he said "Nothing"—I saw my hand<lb></lb>Kerchief half out of his pocket—I asked him if he called that nothing?—he put down his other hand, pulled it out, and dropped it—I took him along till I met a policeman—there was a young man with him, but he left him and crossed the road.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-1386" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1386" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1386" type="surname" value="OSBORN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-1386" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES OSBORN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I received the handkerchief from the prosecutor, and took the prisoner—he denied having it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I was talking to a young man and his wife—I had just bid them good night, and was going home—the gentleman turned round and charged me with picking his pocket—I said I had done no such thing—he give me to the policeman—he turned round about a yard behind him and took the handkerchief up.</p>
